-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-scaled.jpg 1768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-728x906.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-768x956.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-1234x1536.jpg 1234w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-1646x2048.jpg 1646w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-150x187.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1768px) 100vw, 1768px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201768%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-scaled.jpg 1768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-728x906.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-768x956.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-1234x1536.jpg 1234w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-1646x2048.jpg 1646w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-150x187.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-14-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI’ve been making \u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2024/04/italian-chopped-salad/\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ethese grilled garlic baguettes with italian chopped salad\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cspan\u003e for a few years and we LOVE them. It’s such a fun, easy meal and one that really hits the spot. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAnd one day, when I didn’t have any baguettes, I threw some of my pizza dough on the grill instead. I do this weekly but had never topped it with the italian salad. It’s fantastic. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eFirst up: the crust. You don’t HAVE to use a sourdough crust, but it’s easily my favorite. I can’t stop. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"sourdough pizza with italian chopped salad\" width=\"1679\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/italian-chopped-salad-pizza/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Sourdough Pizza with Italian Chopped Salad.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-scaled.jpg 1679w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-728x954.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-768x1006.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-1172x1536.jpg 1172w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-1563x2048.jpg 1563w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-150x197.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1679px) 100vw, 1679px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201679%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-scaled.jpg 1679w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-728x954.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-768x1006.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-1172x1536.jpg 1172w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-1563x2048.jpg 1563w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-150x197.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-2-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eI love this pizza crust so much. You do need to make it the night before, but once it’s mixed, all you have to do is wait. It’s simple and so wonderful. I like to have two or three on hand in the fridge or freezer, so that way if we’re craving pizza, I have this ready to go. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eYes, I still have my classic non-sourdough pizza crust recipe too. But since I feel my sourdough starter daily, I always have discard to use. So I use *fresh* discard for this recipe, meaning the leftover of my starter as soon as it’s re-fed. I haven’t used the discard that has sat in the fridge for awhile, so just keep that in mind. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe sourdough crust is SO chewy and tangy. We all love it – in fact my kids say that it’s their favorite pizza out of any other pizza we order. I either make it on the grill or in a cast iron skillet. Those are my two favorite ways. And they always win. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"sourdough pizza with italian chopped salad\" width=\"1815\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/italian-chopped-salad-pizza/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Sourdough Pizza with Italian Chopped Salad.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-scaled.jpg 1815w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-728x882.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-768x931.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-1267x1536.jpg 1267w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-1690x2048.jpg 1690w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-150x182.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1815px) 100vw, 1815px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201815%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-scaled.jpg 1815w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-728x882.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-768x931.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-1267x1536.jpg 1267w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-1690x2048.jpg 1690w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-150x182.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-3-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eNext up: the salad. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eWe all know my love of chopped salads. The best salad to ever be a salad! Having a bit of everything right there on the spoon is ideal. A chopped salad is elite for that exact reason – you can get a bite of each ingredient, an array of texture, flavor and a drizzle of dressing. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eMy go-to italian chopped salad has salami, chickpeas, iceberg, red onion, tomatoes, roasted red peppers, banana peppers and fresh mozzarella. Oh and smoked provolone cheese! All drizzled with my italian dressing that is super super zesty. I could drink the dressing with a spoon. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan id=\"more-100102\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"sourdough pizza with italian chopped salad\" width=\"1704\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/italian-chopped-salad-pizza/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Sourdough Pizza with Italian Chopped Salad.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-scaled.jpg 1704w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-728x940.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-768x991.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-1190x1536.jpg 1190w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-1587x2048.jpg 1587w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-150x194.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1704px) 100vw, 1704px\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201704%202200\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-scaled.jpg 1704w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-728x940.jpg 728w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-768x991.jpg 768w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-1190x1536.jpg 1190w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-1587x2048.jpg 1587w, https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-150x194.jpg 150w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-4-scaled.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eOf course – you can use any pizza dough that you have. Add other ingredients to your salad too. Make it your own because anytime you have a salad piled high on pizza crust, it will be delish. \u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-7-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"sourdough pizza with italian chopped salad\" width=\"1748\" height=\"2200\" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt=\"\" data-jpibfi-post-url=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/2025/07/italian-chopped-salad-pizza/\" data-jpibfi-post-title=\"Grilled Sourdough Pizza with Italian Chopped Salad.\" data-jpibfi-src=\"https://www.howsweeteats.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/pizza-with-italian-chopped-salad-7-scaled.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.howsweetea